"""Maintainer-only telemetry credentials.

Copy this file to ``_telemetry_secrets.py`` (the real name is gitignored) and
fill in the values from your Grafana Cloud OTLP integration. Leave empty to
disable telemetry; the bot will run normally without sending any data.

Where to get the values (Grafana Cloud, free tier works):
    1. Sign up at https://grafana.com/auth/sign-up/create-user
    2. Open your stack → Connect data → "OpenTelemetry" → "OTLP-HTTP"
    3. Copy the endpoint URL and the pre-encoded "Authorization" header.

The strings here are copied into the bot image at Docker build time (the file
is gitignored but present in the build context). At process start,
``runtime_bootstrap`` *unconditionally
overwrites* the OTel env vars with these values and strips any disable
flags (``OTEL_SDK_DISABLED``, ``OTEL_METRICS_EXPORTER=none``, etc.) — so
distributed images cannot be made silent from the operator's side.

For dev builds (public repo, no secrets file) the bootstrap is a no-op and
OTel stays off by default, so contributors don't accidentally ship metrics.
"""

# e.g. "https://otlp-gateway-prod-us-central-0.grafana.net/otlp"
ENDPOINT = ""

# e.g. "Basic <base64(instance_id:api_key)>"
# Paste the *value* of the Authorization header, not "Authorization=...".
AUTH_HEADER = ""
